value.title: Trump administration removes gray wolf from endangered species list
value.excerpt: The Trump administration is dropping the gray wolf from the endangered species list under the assertion that the animal's population has sufficiently recovered, a move conservation groups decry as shortsighted and promise to challenge in court.

value.title: Biden and Cunningham Hold Slim Leads in North Carolina, Poll Finds
value.excerpt: Joe Biden and Cal Cunningham both led their Republican rivals by three points, a Times/Siena College survey found. Perhaps most notably, 64 percent of respondents said they had already voted.

value.title: Wisconsin GOP says hackers stole $2.3M from Trump reelection fund
value.excerpt: Hackers stole $2.3 million from the Wisconsin Republican Party's account that was being used to help reelect President Donald Trump in the key battleground state, the party's chairman told The Associated Press on Thursday.

value.title: Biden vows to pass LGBTQ rights legislation in first 100 days
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden has promised to make the Equality Act a "top legislative priority" should he win Tuesday’s election.

value.title: Watch: Trump rushes Sen. Martha McSally on stage during Arizona rally
value.excerpt: During a campaign rally in Goodyear, Ariz., President Donald Trump rushed Republican Senator Martha McSally on stage to speak. McSally is in a close Senate race with her Democratic challenger astronaut Mark Kelly.

value.title: They call themselves 'Wives of the Deplorables' because their husbands support Trump

value.title: New Jersey congressman's pledge of 'undying support' for Trump hangs over close House race
value.excerpt: The congressman who represents Atlantic City made a risky political gamble last year. Now he's waiting to see whether it will pay off -- or if he's going home broke.

value.title: Trump uses outdated thinking in attempt to woo suburban women: I'm 'getting your husbands back to work'

value.title: Pence's office says he did not attend swearing-in due to CDC guidelines
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence did not attend Monday night's White House swearing-in ceremony for Supreme Court Justice Amy Coney Barrett because he was adhering to US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention guidelines to prevent the spread of the coronavirus, an administration official told CNN.

value.title: Twitter labels Trump post about mail ballots as ‘disputed’ and ‘misleading’
value.excerpt: The president claimed, without evidence, there were “problems and discrepancies” with mail-in ballots “all over the USA.”

value.title: Judge rejects DOJ's attempt to defend Trump in E. Jean Carroll rape defamation lawsuit
value.excerpt: A federal judge on Tuesday denied the Justice Department's effort to intervene in a defamation lawsuit brought against President Donald Trump by a longtime magazine columnist who has alleged he raped her, paving the way for the case to proceed.

value.title: Stephen Colbert: Mike Pence Is ‘America’s Spare Tire’
value.excerpt: After the White House called the vice president an essential worker, Colbert said: “At best, he is vice essential. You want him in the trunk, but you hope to never have to use him.”

value.excerpt: Prior to becoming a prominent backer of Donald Trump, Kayleigh McEnany praised then-Vice President Joe Biden as "funny and likable" and a "man of the people" who resonates with "middle class voters."

value.title: Pence skips public health recommended self-quarantine but does change plans after staff outbreak

value.title: Trump shirks Covid-19 guidelines while greeting a nearly maskless crowd
value.excerpt: During a campaign stop in Maine, President Donald Trump, without a mask, greeted a largely maskless crowd and signed autographs while in close proximity. CNN medical analyst Dr. Jonathan Reiner says the President's messaging undermines the effort of health professionals advising their patients.

value.title: Brad Pitt narrates new Biden campaign ad airing during World Series

value.title: Analysis: Trump's 'least racist' claim falls flat for many. Yet his campaign still holds appeal for some Black men.
value.excerpt: It's one of those seemingly hard-to-explain things: President Donald Trump holds an allure for some Black men, despite his history of denigrating Black Americans and his refusal to explicitly acknowledge systemic racism.

value.title: Watch: Vice President Mike Pence, Karen Pence vote early in Indianapolis
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence and Karen Pence voted early in the 2020 election in Indianapolis. Pence said it was a "great honor" after dropping his ballot in the box.
